# The real runtime graph, in miniature: a call to the library `Enum.reduce`,
# which dispatches through the `Enumerable` protocol to `List.reduce` and its
# `reduce_cont`/`reduce_step` recursion. The reducer is wrapped in a closure
# that captures the user reducer (`fn (entry, inner) -> {:cont, reducer.(…)} end`),
# so this is the fold_state_machine shape plus one protocol hop.
#
# Under the model the protocol call devirtualizes on the receiver type
# (`list(int)` -> the `List` impl), and the fixpoint settles:
#
#   Enumerable.List.reduce : {:done, int} | {:halted, int}
#   Enum.reduce([1,2,3], 0, +) : int ; settles (no 4096).

fn main() do
  dbg(Enum.reduce([1, 2, 3], 0, fn (x, a) -> x + a end))
end
